title: Tahu Isi
description: This is a popular Indonesian snack made of fried tofu stuffed with a mixture of vegetables like shredded carrot, cabbage, and bean sprouts, often seasoned with garlic, pepper, and sometimes meat or shrimp. These tofu pockets are then dipped in a simple batter and deep-fried until golden and crispy.

title: Bala-Bala
description: Bala-Bala is a traditional Indonesian vegetable fritter. It's made from a mixture of shredded vegetables such as cabbage, carrots, and bean sprouts, combined with a seasoned batter of flour and spices. These fritters are deep-fried until they achieve a crunchy exterior while remaining tender inside.

title: Pisang Goreng
description: Pisang Goreng is essentially fried bananas. Ripe bananas are coated in a batter made from flour and often a hint of sugar and vanilla, then deep-fried until golden brown. These sweet treats are crispy on the outside with a soft, warm banana inside, often served with powdered sugar or chocolate sauce for dipping.
